      "content": "Yellowing leaves, especially on the lower parts of the plant, can be a sign of several issues. One possible cause is a nutrient deficiency, particularly potassium or magnesium, which can cause leaves to turn yellow and drop off. It's also possible that the plant is experiencing root bound conditions or inadequate watering. You may want to check the soil moisture and adjust your watering schedule accordingly. \n\nYou can also try inspecting the soil for any signs of pests or diseases that might be causing the issue. A quick soil test or a consult with a local nursery can provide more specific guidance.",
